        <underline method="pen" type="straight" language="LA" text="Quaere argumenta, siqua potes: nunquam"/>
        <underline method="pen" type="straight" language="LA" text="amicoru[m] iudicio reuincetur"/>
        <underline method="pen" type="straight" language="LA" text="Quia suppeditat nobis vbi &amp; animus ex hoc fore[n]si strepitu reficiatur, &amp; aures co[n]uitio defessae co[n]quiescant"/>
        <underline method="pen" type="straight" language="LA" text="dicamus in ta[n]ta varietate reru[m], nisi animos nostros doctrina excolamus? aut"/>
        <underline method="pen" type="straight" language="LA" text="tanta[m] posse conte[n]tionem, nisi eos doctrina eade[m] relaxemus"/>
        <underline method="pen" type="straight" language="LA" text="siqui ita se literis abdiderunt, vt nihil possint es his neque ad co[m]munem afferre fructu[m], neque in aspectu[m], luc&eacute;mque proferre"/>
        <underline method="pen" type="straight" language="LA" text="meu[m] abstraxerit, aut voluptas auocarit, aut denique somnus retardarit"/>
        <underline method="pen" type="straight" language="LA" text="tandem me reprehe[n]dat, aut quis mihi iure succe[n]seat, si quantu[m] caeteris ad suas res obeundas, quantum ad festos dies ludoru[m] celebrandos, 
            qua[n]tum ad alias volputates, &amp; ad ipsam requiem animi &amp; corporis co[n]ceditur te[m]poris: quantu[m] alii tribuunt te[m]pestiuis co[n]uiuiis, quantum denique aleae, qua[n]tum pilae, 
            tantu[m] mihi egomet ad haec studia recolenda sumpsero?"/>
        <underline method="pen" type="straight" language="LA" text="nunquam amicoru[m] periculis defuit"/>
        <underline method="pen" type="straight" language="LA" text="ex quo fonte hauria[m]"/>
        <underline method="pen" type="straight" language="LA" text="ab adolesce[n]tia"/>
        <underline method="pen" type="straight" language="LA" text="magnopere expete[n]dum, nisi laude[m] atque honestate[m]: in ea aute[m] perseque[n]da omnes crudiatus corporis, omnia pericula mortis atque exilii parui esse duce[n]da: 
            nu[m]quam me pro salute vestra in tot ac tantas dimicationes, atq[ue] in hos profligatoru[m] hominu[m] quotidianos impetus obiecissem. Sed pleni omnes sunt libri, plenae sapientu[m] voces, plena exemploru[m] vetustas, 
            quae iacere[n]t in tenebris omnia, nisi literaru[m] lume[n] accederet. Qu&agrave;m"/>
        <underline method="pen" type="straight" language="LA" text="solum ad intuendu[m]:  veru[m]etiam ad imitandum, fortissimoru[m] viroru[m] expressas, scriptores &amp; Graeci &amp; Latini reliqueru[n]t? 
            quas ego mihi semper in administra[n]da Rep. propone[n]s, animu[m] &amp; mentem mea[m] ipsa cogitatione hominu[m] excellentiu[m] conformaba[m]"/>
        <underline method="pen" type="straight" language="LA" text="Ego multos homines excellenti animo ac virtute fuisse, &amp; sine doctrina, naturae ipsius habitu prop&egrave; diuino, 
            per seipsos &amp; moderatos &amp; graues extitisse fateor. Etia[m] illud adiungo, saepius ad laude[m] atque virtute[m], natura[m] sine doctrina, qu&agrave;m sine natura caluisse doctrina[m]. atque idem ego conte[n]do, 
            cu[m] ad naturam eximia[m] atque illustrem accesserit ratio quaeda[m], co[n]firmati&oacute;que doctrinae, tum illud nescio quid praeclaru[m] ac singulare so[lere]"/>
        <underline method="pen" type="straight" language="LA" text=""/>
        
